Interview Descriptions:
2 rounds interviews with presentations at the final; 
meet lab members for lunch; 
discuss projects with the boss;
sign offer or not
Not much to say, typical interview process in academia

Morning: Meeting with potential supervisor(s);
Noon: Lunch with a grad student;
Afternoon: Meeting with Graduate assistant.
Accommodation expenses: paid.
A few weeks later: an email from the grad assistant informing you which potential supervisors are interested working with you so it is up to you to choose one now. One week time to decide.
